    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Process of making a cast or an impression from a ready made or natural object, particularly part of the body; plaster of Paris frequently used in this technique; sometimes used for creating life masks and death masks.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
